On the other hand, the volume of a cone with radius $r$ and height $h$ is $\frac{\pi}{3} r^2 h$, so the volume of our cone is \[ \frac{\pi}{3} \cdot 3^2 \cdot 4 .\]Therefore the ratio of the volume of the sphere to the volume of the cone is \[ \frac{(4\pi /3) (3/2)^3}{(\pi/3) \cdot 3^2 \cdot 4}
= \frac{4 \cdot 27/8}{9 \cdot 4}
= \boxed{\frac{3}{8}} . \]

